abstract: Government of South Korea announces that deadly outbreak of Middle Eastern respiratory syndrome, which killed 36 people in country and hampered tourism industry, is over.
lead_paragraph: South Korea on Tuesday declared a de facto end to an outbreak of Middle East respiratory syndrome that has killed 26 people.

headline.main: South Korea: Government Declares End to MERS Outbreak
headline.print_headline: Asia; South Korea: Government Declares End to Virus Outbreak
